quran[75]{c,v,t}:
  87,1,"Glorify the name of your Lord, the Most High"
  87,2,Who created and fashioned in due proportion
  87,3,"and Who determined [the creation] then guided them"
  87,4,and Who brings forth the pasture
  87,5,then makes it into withered chaff
  87,6,"We will teach you [the Qur’an], so you will not forget"
  87,7,"except what Allah wills, for indeed He knows what is manifest and what is hidden"
  87,8,We will guide you to the easy way
  87,9,"So remind, if the reminder should benefit"
  87,10,He who fears Allah will take heed
  87,11,but the wretched will avoid it
  87,12,who will enter the Great Fire
  87,13,wherein he will neither die nor live
  87,14,"Indeed, he who purifies himself will attain success"
  87,15,and remembers his Lord’s Name and prays
  87,16,But you prefer the life of this world
  87,17,even though the Hereafter is better and more lasting
  87,18,"Indeed, this was in the earlier Scriptures"
  87,19,the Scriptures of Abraham and Moses
  88,1,Has there come to you the story of the Overwhelming Event
  88,2,"On that Day, some faces will be humiliated"
  88,3,toiling and weary
  88,4,as they burn in a scorching Fire
  88,5,They will be made to drink from a boiling spring
  88,6,and they will have no food except bitter thorny plants
  88,7,that neither nourishes nor satisfies hunger
  88,8,Other faces on that Day will be joyful
  88,9,well-pleased with their past striving
  88,10,in an elevated garden
  88,11,wherein no idle talk will be heard
  88,12,There will be a flowing spring
  88,13,and couches raised high
  88,14,and cups placed ready
  88,15,and cushions lined up
  88,16,and splendid carpets spread out
  88,17,"Do they not reflect on the camel, how it is created"
  88,18,"and the sky, how it is raised high"
  88,19,"and the mountains, how they are firmly set up"
  88,20,"and the earth, how it is spread out"
  88,21,"So remind [O Prophet]; your duty is only to remind"
  88,22,you are not assigned to compel them
  88,23,But whoever turns away and disbelieves
  88,24,Allah will inflict upon him the greatest punishment
  88,25,"Indeed, to Us is their return"
  88,26,then it is for Us to call them to account
  89,1,By the dawn
  89,2,and the ten nights
  89,3,and the even and the odd
  89,4,and by the night when it comes
  89,5,are these oaths not sufficient for those who have sense
  89,6,Have you not considered how your Lord dealt with ‘Ād
  89,7,"of Iram, who were people of great stature"
  89,8,the like of whom had never been created in the land
  89,9,"and Thamūd, who carved out the rocks in the Valley"
  89,10,and the mighty and powerful Pharaoh
  89,11,All of them transgressed in the land
  89,12,and spread therein much corruption
  89,13,so your Lord poured upon them a scourge of punishment
  89,14,"Indeed, your Lord is ever vigilant"
  89,15,"As for man, when he is tested by his Lord by honoring him and bestowing blessings upon him, he says, “My Lord has [deservedly] honored me!”"
  89,16,"But when he is tested by restricting his provision, he says, “My Lord has [undeservedly] humiliated me!”"
  89,17,No indeed! You are not kind to the orphan
  89,18,nor do you urge one another to feed the needy
  89,19,and you greedily consume the entire inheritance
  89,20,and love wealth immensely
  89,21,No indeed! When the earth is crushed over and over
  89,22,"and your Lord comes with the angels, rank after rank"
  89,23,"and Hell is brought near on that Day – this is when man will understand, but what is the use of that understanding"
  89,24,"He will say, “Would that I had sent forth something for my [eternal] life!”"
  89,25,None can punish as He punishes on that Day
  89,26,and none can bind as He binds
  89,27,"[It will be said to the believer,] “O the tranquil soul"
  89,28,"Return to your Lord, well pleased and pleasing [to Him]"
  89,29,"Join My [righteous] slaves"
  89,30,and enter My Paradise.”